Fall 2023 ISL Team Registration Opened 6/19/2023

Important Note: If the soccer complex/facility is listed below for the date of your game there may be possible changes to your status/location. It doesn’t necessary mean your game is cancelled. Please refer to your individual schedules for any updates. All information on your schedule will reflect any changes that may have occurred. You will also receive an email and/or text message (if opted in for text messaging) regarding any changes to your individual game as soon as ISL is notified and able to communicate with you

Coaches/Managers: For games that are affected due to weather or field conditions, every effort will be made to reschedule (move) the games on the original date to avoid cancelling the game. In the event that Indiana Soccer cancels a game, teams need to communicate with each other to come up with a rescheduled date/time and/or location and submit this change via a support ticket. No fee will be assessed for games ISL cancels due to weather and/or field conditions.

Important Documents (including the rules) and How To Webinars

2023-2024 ISL League Fees Per Team

Important Note: Please include club, age group, and team name on check when submitting so your team payment can be accurately recorded

Mail Payments to: Indiana Soccer

19000 Grand Park Blvd.

Suite J

Westfield, IN 46074

Fall 2023-Spring 2024 Referees Fees

Referee Pay Chart for 2023 – 2024 – Each team is to bring ½ of the fee in cash in denominations that do not require the referees to make change. Only pay the referees who are in attendance. If one referee does not show, the teams keep that referee’s fee. If the game does not start due to weather and is not played, the referees do not get paid. If the game begins but is called because of weather, the referees keep their fees. Referees are to be paid prior to kick off.
